content_chunks.content: This course provides an in-depth examination of indoor air quality (IAQ) and thermal comfort, focusing on the requirements and assessment techniques. Students will learn about key IAQ and comfort metrics, measurement tools, regulatory standards, and digital skills essential for effective monitoring and assessment. The course includes hands-on training with modeling and simulation software to optimize indoor environments in various building types, highlighting practical applications in ensuring health and comfort in housing.

Technology for indoor environmental monitoring and thermal comfort optimization - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in indoor air quality (IAQ) fundamentals and thermal comfort principles using advanced assessment methods and monitoring tools. Students will master IAQ assessment methods, thermal comfort monitoring techniques, and data analysis techniques for optimizing indoor environmental conditions. The curriculum focuses on practical IAQ optimization strategies, thermal comfort optimization approaches, and IAQ modeling software integration for building IAQ integration projects. Participants will gain hands-on experience with thermal comfort simulation tools, IAQ regulatory standards compliance, and comfort standards implementation using digital IAQ assessment tools. The program emphasizes health impact assessment methodologies, smart building technologies integration, and IAQ cost-benefit analysis for ensuring optimal indoor environmental quality in diverse building types.
